I whole heartily agree with Tom's concept of the &quot;Protestor's Memorial&quot; and also find a smiggen of comfort and solice that those who went and died in Vietnam contributed to how and when we engage others on the battle field. It is too bad that we cannot count the number of lives saved by using this formula.
